        "content": "<p>Suppose I have a variable which was introduces with a <code>let</code>. I proved some things about it, and now I no longer care about its value, so I want to <code>generalize</code> it away. Is there a way to just remove the <code>let</code> data?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">generalize</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span>\n<span class=\"n\">clear</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span>\n<span class=\"n\">generalize</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span>\n<span class=\"n\">clear</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B'</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>works, but it's quite long and ugly</p>",
